cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper is about Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves understanding both visual content and textual content. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the visual and textual aspects of VQA. However, since the paper also proposes a deep learning model, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely categories. Finally, since VQA involves retrieving information from images and text, cs.IR is a possible category as well.
